        <h2 class="artical-title">Lab-Grown Diamonds – The Science Behind the Process</h2>
        <p>Scientists have tried replicating the natural diamond process for several years now. Even though experiments started as early as 1893, the lab-grown processes used today were first formulated around 1954. After years of perfecting the process, lab-grown diamonds can now easily be created in one of two ways. Based on the process used, lab-grown diamonds can be of two types – High Pressure High Temperature (HPHT) or Chemical Vapour Deposition (CVD).</p>
